refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolcurl_setopt CurlHandlehandle intoption mixedvalue
Sets an option on the given cURL session handle.

&reftitle.parameters;
&curl.ch.description;
option
The CURLOPT_* option to set.
value
The value to be set on option. See the description of the CURLOPT_* constants for details on the type of values each constant expects.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Initializing a new cURL session and fetching a web page


<?php
// create a new cURL resource
$ch = curl_init();

// set URL and other appropriate options
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, "http://www.example.com/");
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HEADER, false);

// grab URL and pass it to the browser
curl_exec($ch);

// close cURL resource, and free up system resources
curl_close($ch);
?>
